{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HRCZdSM6WGcqr5MUqvvsiT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 3 nodes are up and ready on v24.1.0. Now I'll perform the controlled partitioned rolling update to v24.1.1.\n\nThe StatefulSet already has `partition: 2` set (from the resource file). A partitioned rolling update works by:\n1. Setting partition=3 (no pods updated) → update image → pods roll out one at a time as partition decreases\n2. Or simply patching the image and using partition to gate the rollout\n\nThe clean approach: patch the image to v24.1.1 with partition=3 (no pods auto-updated), then step the partition down from 3→2→1→0."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":279,"cache_read_input_tokens":47628,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":279},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"da14e5d7-16f1-4dd1-b050-86175e27b13d","uuid":"c6635956-18d8-4a7c-94ed-1e0a61c5aa33","request_id":"req_011Cc49Ve5NdE2RZPcEUzyrd"}
